SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3112
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE PHELPS.
5966H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 571, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to the conceal-carry
rights of retired law enforcement officers.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 571, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 571.165, to read as follows:
571.165. 1. As used in this section, the following terms mean:
2 (1) "Law enforcement agency", the same meaning given to the term in section
3 590.1040;
4 (2) "Retired law enforcement identification card", an identification card issued
5 by a law enforcement agency to a retired officer for purposes of verifying the retired
6 officer's satisfaction of certain eligibility requirements to carry a concealed firearm in
7 accordance with 18 U.S.C. Section 926C;
8 (3) "Retired officer", any individual separated from service with a law
9 enforcement agency who meets the requirements of paragraphs (1), (2), (3), (5), and (7)
10 of subsection (c) of 18 U.S.C. Section 926C.
11 2. A law enforcement agency shall provide any retired officer with a retired law
12 enforcement identification card upon the payment of a fee of one hundred dollars.
13 3. A retired law enforcement identification card issued under this section shall
14 include at least the following:
15 (1) The photograph of the retired officer;
16 (2) The name, address, date of birth, and signature of the retired officer;
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

HB 3112 2
17 (3) The name, telephone number, and address of the law enforcement agency
18 issuing the card;
19 (4) The following text: "This card does not authorize the holder to carry a
20 concealed firearm in accordance with 18 U.S.C. Section 926C unless accompanied by a
21 firearms qualification certification obtained within the most recent twelve-month period
22 that meets the requirements of 18 U.S.C. Section 926C.";
23 (5) The following text: "This card does not authorize the holder to carry a
24 concealed firearm while under the influence of alcohol or another intoxicating or
25 hallucinatory drug or substance.";
26 (6) The following text: "This card does not authorize the holder to act on the
27 named law enforcement agency's behalf or to exercise any law enforcement authority.";
28 and
29 (7) A statement that the card has an indefinite expiration date.
30 4. A law enforcement agency shall maintain a roster of its retired officers issued
31 law enforcement identification cards under this section.
32 5. A law enforcement agency shall reissue any lost retired law enforcement
33 identification card upon the payment of a fee of one hundred fifty dollars.
34 6. A law enforcement agency may, but shall not be required to, offer retired
35 officers the firearms training required to maintain the certification described in
36 subsection (c) of 18 U.S.C. Section 926C.
37 7. A law enforcement agency that collects any fees under this section shall use
38 the fees to conduct activities required or authorized under this section.
